<TITLE> Tk 700mln for expat welfare </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, June 10 (bdnews24.com)  The finance minister proposed a to spend Tk 700 million for 'Expat Welfare and Skills Development Fund'. It is the same as current fiscal year's allocation. "This fund will be used for creating employment opportunities in the world," AMA Muhith said in his speech. "Additionally the skills of the workers within the country will also be developed through this," he added. "In spite of the world recession and various restrictions, around 0.48 million workers were recruited abroad in 2009." The target for sending workers abroad is set at 0.577 million during the 2010-2011 fiscal, said the minister. "In addition, the cabinet has already approved an act to found banking company under government management. "As a result, 'Expatriate Welfare Bank Limited' can be founded sooner," he said. bdnew
